result.name: McDonald's

reviews.text: Came at 9.30 before the shops were open. Food was pretty standard. Was unsatisfied with the fact that there were only 2 online order screens activated when 4 or 5 were available since they had a considerable amount of customers in line to order. McCafe is pretty good too and you can order food and substitute a drink from the Cafe with an extra charge if you wish.

Felt disgraced when ordering the afternoon tea set.  When I ordered 抹茶豆漿，that tall guy answered me with an unfriendly tone.  He said ‘we don't have 豆漿 here ’. So I have to point to the picture of Soy milk Mstcha and he answered with a loud tone ‘ that is called 豆奶抹茶!’ In order not to get wrong again, I pointed to the stuffed bread to show what I want.  The guy asked `係未yee Sic Boa" but I couldn't understand what that means.  He then gave me the menu in a very rude way.
After that, he played with his cell phone continuously and reheated the bread at the same time.

I was definitely not ‘loving it’ at this McDonald’s. The manager at the Mc Cafe counter is the RUDEST employee I have ever come across. You’d get better service at the morgue. Horrible attitude. Asked him for a few napkins and he literally threw them at my face. When I asked him if he was the manager he actually had the audacity to pretend that he wasn’t. Everything else was adequate but the customer service was wayyy below standards and the Store manager should do something about it.
Great location at TST area. With shopping arcade surround the mccafe 👍
Burgers were good considering the price. The self service ordering kiosks were not really that user friendly and seemed to be more geared to making you order more. An OK choice for an OK snack.
